  38 def reorder_source_keys(data):
  39     # type: (tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument) -> tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument
  40     sources = []  # type: sources_type
  41     for source_key in ["source", "sources"]:
  42         sources.extend(data.get(source_key, tomlkit.aot()).value)
  43     new_source_aot = tomlkit.aot()
  44     for entry in sources:
  45         table = tomlkit.table()  # type: tomlkit.items.Table
  46         source_entry = PipfileLoader.populate_source(entry.copy())
  47         for key in ["name", "url", "verify_ssl"]:
  48             table.update({key: source_entry[key]})
  49         new_source_aot.append(table)
  50     data["source"] = new_source_aot
  51     if data.get("sources", None):
  52         del data["sources"]
  53     return data

  56 class PipfileLoader(plette.pipfiles.Pipfile):
  57     @classmethod
  58     def validate(cls, data):
  59         # type: (tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument) -> None
  60         for key, klass in plette.pipfiles.PIPFILE_SECTIONS.items():
  61             if key not in data or key == "sources":
  62                 continue
  63             try:
  64                 klass.validate(data[key])
  65             except Exception:
  66                 pass
  67 
  68     @classmethod
  69     def ensure_package_sections(cls, data):
  70         # type: (tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument[Text, Any]) -> tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument[Text, Any]
  71         """
  72         Ensure that all pipfile package sections are present in the given toml document
  73 
  74         :param :class:`~tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument` data: The toml document to
  75             ensure package sections are present on
  76         :return: The updated toml document, ensuring ``packages`` and ``dev-packages``
  77             sections are present
  78         :rtype: :class:`~tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument`
  79         """
  80         package_keys = (
  81             k for k in plette.pipfiles.PIPFILE_SECTIONS.keys() if k.endswith("packages")
  82         )
  83         for key in package_keys:
  84             if key not in data:
  85                 data.update({key: tomlkit.table()})
  86         return data
  87 
  88     @classmethod
  89     def populate_source(cls, source):
  90         """Derive missing values of source from the existing fields."""
  91         # Only URL pararemter is mandatory, let the KeyError be thrown.
  92         if "name" not in source:
  93             source["name"] = get_url_name(source["url"])
  94         if "verify_ssl" not in source:
  95             source["verify_ssl"] = "https://" in source["url"]
  96         if not isinstance(source["verify_ssl"], bool):
  97             source["verify_ssl"] = str(source["verify_ssl"]).lower() == "true"
  98         return source
  99 
 100     @classmethod
 101     def load(cls, f, encoding=None):
 102         # type: (Any, Text) -> PipfileLoader
 103         content = f.read()
 104         if encoding is not None:
 105             content = content.decode(encoding)
 106         _data = tomlkit.loads(content)
 107         should_reload = "source" not in _data
 108         _data = reorder_source_keys(_data)
 109         if should_reload:
 110             if "sources" in _data:
 111                 content = tomlkit.dumps(_data)
 112             else:
 113                 # HACK: There is no good way to prepend a section to an existing
 114                 # TOML document, but there's no good way to copy non-structural
 115                 # content from one TOML document to another either. Modify the
 116                 # TOML content directly, and load the new in-memory document.
 117                 sep = "" if content.startswith("\n") else "\n"
 118                 content = plette.pipfiles.DEFAULT_SOURCE_TOML + sep + content
 119         data = tomlkit.loads(content)
 120         data = cls.ensure_package_sections(data)
 121         instance = cls(data)
 122         instance._data = dict(instance._data)
 123         return instance
 124 
 125     def __contains__(self, key):
 126         # type: (Text) -> bool
 127         if key not in self._data:
 128             package_keys = self._data.get("packages", {}).keys()
 129             dev_package_keys = self._data.get("dev-packages", {}).keys()
 130             return any(key in pkg_list for pkg_list in (package_keys, dev_package_keys))
 131         return True
 132 
 133     def __getattribute__(self, key):
 134         # type: (Text) -> Any
 135         if key == "source":
 136             return self._data[key]
 137         return super(PipfileLoader, self).__getattribute__(key)

 140 @attr.s(slots=True)
 141 class Pipfile(object):
 142     path = attr.ib(validator=is_path, type=Path)
 143     projectfile = attr.ib(validator=is_projectfile, type=ProjectFile)
 144     _pipfile = attr.ib(type=PipfileLoader)
 145     _pyproject = attr.ib(
 146         default=attr.Factory(tomlkit.document), type=tomlkit.toml_document.TOMLDocument
 147     )
 148     build_system = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(dict), type=dict)
 149     _requirements = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(list), type=list)
 150     _dev_requirements = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(list), type=list)

 152     @path.default
 153     def _get_path(self):
 154         # type: () -> Path
 155         return Path(os.curdir).absolute()
 156 
 157     @projectfile.default
 158     def _get_projectfile(self):
 159         # type: () -> ProjectFile
 160         return self.load_projectfile(os.curdir, create=False)

 162     @_pipfile.default
 163     def _get_pipfile(self):
 164         # type: () -> Union[plette.pipfiles.Pipfile, PipfileLoader]
 165         return self.projectfile.model

 167     @property

 171     @property
 172     def extended_keys(self):
 173         return [
 174             k
 175             for k in itertools.product(
 176                 ("packages", "dev-packages"), ("", "vcs", "editable")
 177             )
 178         ]

 180     @property
 181     def pipfile(self):
 182         # type: () -> Union[PipfileLoader, plette.pipfiles.Pipfile]
 183         return self._pipfile

 185     def get_deps(self, dev=False, only=True):
 186         # type: (bool, bool) -> Dict[Text, Dict[Text, Union[List[Text], Text]]]
 187         deps = {}  # type: Dict[Text, Dict[Text, Union[List[Text], Text]]]
 188         if dev:
 189             deps.update(dict(self.pipfile._data.get("dev-packages", {})))
 190             if only:
 191                 return deps
 192         return tomlkit_value_to_python(
 193             merge_items([deps, dict(self.pipfile._data.get("packages", {}))])
 194         )
 195 
 196     def get(self, k):
 197         # type: (Text) -> Any
 198         return self.__getitem__(k)
 199 
 200     def __contains__(self, k):
 201         # type: (Text) -> bool
 202         check_pipfile = k in self.extended_keys or self.pipfile.__contains__(k)
 203         if check_pipfile:
 204             return True
 205         return False
 206 
 207     def __getitem__(self, k, *args, **kwargs):
 208         # type: ignore
 209         retval = None
 210         pipfile = self._pipfile
 211         section = None
 212         pkg_type = None
 213         try:
 214             retval = pipfile[k]
 215         except KeyError:
 216             if "-" in k:
 217                 section, _, pkg_type = k.rpartition("-")
 218                 vals = getattr(pipfile.get(section, {}), "_data", {})
 219                 vals = tomlkit_value_to_python(vals)
 220                 if pkg_type == "vcs":
 221                     retval = {k: v for k, v in vals.items() if is_vcs(v)}
 222                 elif pkg_type == "editable":
 223                     retval = {k: v for k, v in vals.items() if is_editable(v)}
 224             if retval is None:
 225                 raise
 226         else:
 227             retval = getattr(retval, "_data", retval)
 228         return retval
 229 
 230     def __getattr__(self, k, *args, **kwargs):
 231         # type: ignore
 232         retval = None
 233         pipfile = super(Pipfile, self).__getattribute__("_pipfile")
 234         try:
 235             retval = super(Pipfile, self).__getattribute__(k)
 236         except AttributeError:
 237             retval = getattr(pipfile, k, None)
 238         if retval is not None:
 239             return retval
 240         return super(Pipfile, self).__getattribute__(k, *args, **kwargs)

 256     @classmethod
 257     def read_projectfile(cls, path):
 258         # type: (Text) -> ProjectFile
 259         """Read the specified project file and provide an interface for writing/updating.
 260 
 261         :param Text path: Path to the target file.
 262         :return: A project file with the model and location for interaction
 263         :rtype: :class:`~requirementslib.models.project.ProjectFile`
 264         """
 265         pf = ProjectFile.read(path, PipfileLoader, invalid_ok=True)
 266         return pf
 267 
 268     @classmethod
 269     def load_projectfile(cls, path, create=False):
 270         # type: (Text, bool) -> ProjectFile
 271         """
 272         Given a path, load or create the necessary pipfile.
 273 
 274         :param Text path: Path to the project root or pipfile
 275         :param bool create: Whether to create the pipfile if not found, defaults to True
 276         :raises OSError: Thrown if the project root directory doesn't exist
 277         :raises FileNotFoundError: Thrown if the pipfile doesn't exist and ``create=False``
 278         :return: A project file instance for the supplied project
 279         :rtype: :class:`~requirementslib.models.project.ProjectFile`
 280         """
 281         if not path:
 282             raise RuntimeError("Must pass a path to classmethod 'Pipfile.load'")
 283         if not isinstance(path, Path):
 284             path = Path(path).absolute()
 285         pipfile_path = path if path.is_file() else path.joinpath("Pipfile")
 286         project_path = pipfile_path.parent
 287         if not project_path.exists():
 288             raise FileNotFoundError("%s is not a valid project path!" % path)
 289         elif not pipfile_path.exists() or not pipfile_path.is_file():
 290             if not create:
 291                 raise RequirementError("%s is not a valid Pipfile" % pipfile_path)
 292         return cls.read_projectfile(pipfile_path.as_posix())
 293 
 294     @classmethod
 295     def load(cls, path, create=False):
 296         # type: (Text, bool) -> Pipfile
 297         """
 298         Given a path, load or create the necessary pipfile.
 299 
 300         :param Text path: Path to the project root or pipfile
 301         :param bool create: Whether to create the pipfile if not found, defaults to True
 302         :raises OSError: Thrown if the project root directory doesn't exist
 303         :raises FileNotFoundError: Thrown if the pipfile doesn't exist and ``create=False``
 304         :return: A pipfile instance pointing at the supplied project
 305         :rtype:: class:`~requirementslib.models.pipfile.Pipfile`
 306         """
 307 
 308         projectfile = cls.load_projectfile(path, create=create)
 309         pipfile = projectfile.model
 310         creation_args = {
 311             "projectfile": projectfile,
 312             "pipfile": pipfile,
 313             "path": Path(projectfile.location),
 314         }
 315         return cls(**creation_args)
 316 
 317     def write(self):
 318         # type: () -> None
 319         self.projectfile.model = copy.deepcopy(self._pipfile)
 320         self.projectfile.write()

 329         # type: () -> List[Requirement]

 332     @property
 333     def dev_requirements(self):
 334         # type: () -> List[Requirement]
 335         if not self._dev_requirements:
 336             packages = tomlkit_value_to_python(self.pipfile.get("dev-packages", {}))
 337             self._dev_requirements = [
 338                 Requirement.from_pipfile(k, v)
 339                 for k, v in packages.items()
 340                 if v is not None
 341             ]
 342         return self._dev_requirements
 343 
 344     @property
 345     def requirements(self):
 346         # type: () -> List[Requirement]
 347         if not self._requirements:
 348             packages = tomlkit_value_to_python(self.pipfile.get("packages", {}))
 349             self._requirements = [
 350                 Requirement.from_pipfile(k, v)
 351                 for k, v in packages.items()
 352                 if v is not None
 353             ]
 354         return self._requirements

 356     def _read_pyproject(self):
 357         # type: () -> None
 358         pyproject = self.path.parent.joinpath("pyproject.toml")
 359         if pyproject.exists():
 360             self._pyproject = tomlkit.loads(pyproject.read_text())
 361             build_system = self._pyproject.get("build-system", None)
 362             if build_system and not build_system.get("build_backend"):
 363                 build_system["build-backend"] = "setuptools.build_meta:__legacy__"
 364             elif not build_system or not build_system.get("requires"):
 365                 build_system = {
 366                     "requires": ["setuptools>=40.8", "wheel"],
 367                     "build-backend": "setuptools.build_meta:__legacy__",
 368                 }
 369             self.build_system = build_system
 370 
 371     @property
 372     def build_requires(self):
 373         # type: () -> List[Text]
 374         if not self.build_system:
 375             self._read_pyproject()
 376         return self.build_system.get("requires", [])
 377 
 378     @property
 379     def build_backend(self):
 380         # type: () -> Text
 381         pyproject = self.path.parent.joinpath("pyproject.toml")
 382         if not self.build_system:
 383             self._read_pyproject()
 384         return self.build_system.get("build-backend", None)
